juniMRouterMIB.name: juniMRouterMIB

revisions.description: Extended the ipMRouteInterfaceEntry Table, introduced traps and platform dependent juniMRoutePortTable.
Scalar attribute juniMcastRpfDisable is supported in this MIB module.
Initial version of this MIB module.

juniMRouterMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@Juniper.net
juniMRouterMIB.description: The IP multicast router MIB for Juniper Networks enterprise.

juniMcastRpfRouteTable.name: juniMcastRpfRouteTable
juniMcastRpfRouteTable.description: The table listing the static IP routes for the mcast RPF check.

juniMcastRpfRouteEntry.name: juniMcastRpfRouteEntry
juniMcastRpfRouteEntry.description: An entry representing the static IP route for the mcast RPF check.

juniMcastRouteStaticMask.name: juniMcastRouteStaticMask
juniMcastRouteStaticMask.description: The static group's destination IpAddress Mask.

juniMcastRouteStaticTag.name: juniMcastRouteStaticTag
juniMcastRouteStaticTag.description: The tag value to be associated.

juniMcastRouteStaticRowStatus.name: juniMcastRouteStaticRowStatus
juniMcastRouteStaticRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniMcastRouteStaticRowStatus juniMcastRouteStaticDest juniMcastRouteStaticMask juniMcastRouteStaticRtPreference juniMcastRouteStaticRpfHop juniMcastRouteStaticTag

juniMRouteTable.name: juniMRouteTable
juniMRouteTable.description: The table containing the extended information of IP Multicast Route Entry

juniMRouteEntry.name: juniMRouteEntry
juniMRouteEntry.description: An entry representing the additional information of IP Multicast Route Entry

juniMRouteAdmBw.name: juniMRouteAdmBw
juniMRouteAdmBw.description: Multicast Admission Control bandwidth in bps.

juniMRouteQosBwAdaptive.name: juniMRouteQosBwAdaptive
juniMRouteQosBwAdaptive.description: Indicates that qos bandwidth is measured.

juniMRouteIsEcmp.name: juniMRouteIsEcmp
juniMRouteIsEcmp.description: Indicates RPF route is an ECMP route.

juniMRouteRpfDisabled.name: juniMRouteRpfDisabled
juniMRouteRpfDisabled.description: Indicates that RPF check is disabled for this entry.

juniMRoutePktFwd.name: juniMRoutePktFwd
juniMRoutePktFwd.description: Packets received that made it out on any egress.

juniMcastRpfDisable.name: juniMcastRpfDisable
juniMcastRpfDisable.description: Disable RPF check for the Group access list name. Null value for enabling RPF check for the access list.

juniMRouteInterfaceTable.name: juniMRouteInterfaceTable
juniMRouteInterfaceTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing multicast routing information specific to interfaces.

juniMRouteInterfaceEntry.name: juniMRouteInterfaceEntry
juniMRouteInterfaceEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the multicast routing information for a particular interface.

juniMRouteInterfaceActiveGroups.name: juniMRouteInterfaceActiveGroups
juniMRouteInterfaceActiveGroups.description: This indicates the total number of groups currently forwarded on the interface.

juniMRouteInterfaceBlockedGroups.name: juniMRouteInterfaceBlockedGroups
juniMRouteInterfaceBlockedGroups.description: This indicates the total number of groups currently blocked on the interface.

juniMroutePortLocationType.name: juniMroutePortLocationType
juniMroutePortLocationType.description: Describes the interpretation of JuniInterfaceLocationValue object values into platform-dependent interface location components, e.g., 'slot.port' on an ERX.

juniMRoutePortTable.name: juniMRoutePortTable
juniMRoutePortTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing multicast routing information specific to the number of mroutes (across all VRs) , that have OIFs, on a port.

juniMRoutePortEntry.name: juniMRoutePortEntry
juniMRoutePortEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the multicast routing information specific to the number of mroutes (across all VRs) , that have OIFs, on a port.

juniMRoutePortLocationIndex.name: juniMRoutePortLocationIndex
juniMRoutePortLocationIndex.description: The value of a platform specific port location.

juniMRoutePortMaxBw.name: juniMRoutePortMaxBw
juniMRoutePortMaxBw.description: Maximum port admission-bandwidth-limit to be configured on the port.

juniMRoutePortPriorityBw.name: juniMRoutePortPriorityBw
juniMRoutePortPriorityBw.description: Maximum port priority-bandwidth-limit to be configured on the port.

juniMRoutePortHysteresis.name: juniMRoutePortHysteresis
juniMRoutePortHysteresis.description: Hysteresis to be configured on the port. Applies to juniMRoutePortMaxBw and juniMRoutePortPriorityBw.

juniMRoutePortSGCount.name: juniMRoutePortSGCount
juniMRoutePortSGCount.description: Number of mroutes on this port.

juniMRoutePortLimit.name: juniMRoutePortLimit
juniMRoutePortLimit.description: Limit on the number of mroutes, with the OIFs on the port, to be configured on the port .

juniMRoutePortBwExceded.name: juniMRoutePortBwExceded
juniMRoutePortBwExceded.description: A juniMRoutePortBwExceded trap signifies the port max admission limit are exceded. This trap should be generated when the OIFs are blocked due to exceded admission limit on the port.

juniMRoutePortBwReceded.name: juniMRoutePortBwReceded
juniMRoutePortBwReceded.description: A juniMRoutePortBwReceded trap signifies the port max admission limit are receded. This trap should be generated when the the port admission limits fall below the configured hysteresis value on the port.

juniMRoutePortPriorityBwExceded.name: juniMRoutePortPriorityBwExceded
juniMRoutePortPriorityBwExceded.description: A juniMRoutePortPriorityBwExceded trap signifies the port priority admission limit are exceded. This trap should be generated when the OIFs are blocked due to exceded admission limit on the port.

juniMRoutePortPriorityBwReceded.name: juniMRoutePortPriorityBwReceded
juniMRoutePortPriorityBwReceded.description: A juniMRoutePortPriorityReceded trap signifies the port priority admission limit are receded. This trap should be generated when the the port admission limits fall below the configured hysteresis value on the port.

juniMRouteIfLocIndex.name: juniMRouteIfLocIndex
juniMRouteIfLocIndex.description: The interface location on which the mrouter trap is generated.

juniMcastCompliance.name: juniMcastCompliance
juniMcastCompliance.description: Obsolete compliance statement for entities which implement the Juniper multicast MIB. This statement became obsolete when juniMRouteTable were added.

juniMcastCompliance2.name: juniMcastCompliance2
juniMcastCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Juniper multicast MIB.

juniMcastCompliance3.name: juniMcastCompliance3
juniMcastCompliance3.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Juniper multicast MIB.This statement became obsolete when juniMRouteInterfaceTable, juniMRoutePortTable and mrouter traps were added.

juniMcastCompliance4.name: juniMcastCompliance4
juniMcastCompliance4.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Juniper multicast MIB.

juniMcastRpfRouteConfGroup.name: juniMcastRpfRouteConfGroup
juniMcastRpfRouteConfGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management of multicast RPF static routes of the product.

juniMRouteConfGroup.name: juniMRouteConfGroup
juniMRouteConfGroup.description: A collection of objects providing extended information of IP Multicast Route Entry.

juniMcastGlobalConfGroup.name: juniMcastGlobalConfGroup
juniMcastGlobalConfGroup.description: A collection of global scalar objects providing extended information of IP Multicast Route Entry.

juniMRoutePortConfGroup.name: juniMRoutePortConfGroup
juniMRoutePortConfGroup.description: A collection of objects providing extended information of IP Multicast Route Entry.
